Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:13.120 --> 00:00:14.510
&gt;&gt; Grant Harris: Good
evening, everyone.

00:00:14.510 --> 00:00:16.690
I'm very happy to see
all of you tonight.

00:00:16.690 --> 00:00:18.550
My name is Grant Harris.

00:00:18.550 --> 00:00:21.820
I'm chief of the European
Division here at the Library.

00:00:21.820 --> 00:00:23.300
We're now in the
Madison building,

00:00:23.300 --> 00:00:26.580
but the European Division is
over in the Jefferson building,

00:00:26.580 --> 00:00:29.330
the oldest of the
three buildings.

00:00:31.190 --> 00:00:35.650
The mic is on, all right.

00:00:35.650 --> 00:00:39.910
Okay. So what we're here
tonight for is for the symposium

00:00:39.910 --> 00:00:45.060
on Italian Americans before
and during World War II.

00:00:45.060 --> 00:00:49.540
The European Division is very
pleased to cosponsor this event

00:00:49.540 --> 00:00:53.290
with the greater
Washington DC region

00:00:53.290 --> 00:00:56.810
of the National Organization
of Italian American Women.

00:00:56.810 --> 00:00:59.120
That's a long mouthful for me.

00:00:59.120 --> 00:01:01.790
That organization
gets all the credit.

00:01:01.790 --> 00:01:03.170
I like to take credit
for things,

00:01:03.170 --> 00:01:05.050
but that organization
takes all the credit

00:01:05.050 --> 00:01:07.920
for initiating this
event and bringing

00:01:07.920 --> 00:01:12.180
to us tonight three really
distinguished speakers.

00:01:12.180 --> 00:01:16.360
So now a little housekeeping,
I remind you now

00:01:16.360 --> 00:01:20.130
to turn off your cell
phones and recording devices

00:01:20.130 --> 00:01:23.610
for the duration
of this program.

00:01:23.610 --> 00:01:28.500
Also, please note that this
event is being recorded

00:01:28.500 --> 00:01:32.290
for a future Library
of Congress webcast.

